    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-07-24T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-07-24T19:00:00-05:00" n="870"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d870">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 341.622a/192a</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Acting <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PWH1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Page</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-07-24T19:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 24, 1916, 7 p. m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3562. Your 4252,<note n="1" xml:id="d870fn1">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_640">p. 640</ref>.</note> May
                    5, and 4335,<note n="2" xml:id="d870fn2">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_646">p. 646</ref>.</note> May
                    20. Please cable immediately whether all of the Germans taken from the S. S. <hi
                        rend="italic">China</hi> have been released.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_PFL1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
